  Description: 'Wound: Face scorched by flaming pitch, skin peeling, one eye burned
    shut.


    Story: Yusuf, a captured Ottoman janissary pressed into carrying
    supplies, claws at his ruined face. His cries are half in Turkish, half in desperate
    Maltese, begging not to be left to rot. He has no kin here, no banner to return
    to, only terror that his name will be forgotten, his body unburied.



    Required
    bandages to heal: 5'
